com.ti.ccstudio.scripting.environment

Class TraceLevel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ti.ccstudio.scripting.environment.TraceLevel

  • public class TraceLevel
extends java.lang.Object
    Debug Server Scripting uses the logging functionality built-in to Java version 1.4 (and higher) to implement logging to the console (stdout and stderr) as well as to a file. A series of standard logging levels are defined that can be used to control logging output. The levels in descending order are:
    • OFF (turn off logging)
    • SEVERE (highest value)
    • WARNING
    • INFO
    • CONFIG
    • FINE
    • FINER
    • FINEST
    • FINEST (lowest value)
    • ALL (log all messages)
    Using these values in combination with the the methods traceSetFileLevel and traceSetConsoleLevel it is possible to individually customize which messages get logged to the console and which messges get logged to a file.
